Frequently Asked Questions

What is the distinction between an estimate and a design contract?

An estimate is a cost assessment that is crafted for your project. When you finish a major refurbishment, the price is for the complete work. The cost of the project may fluctuate as you progress through the design phase.

A design arrangement indicates that you have chosen Roberts General Contractors as your building contractor but are not certain of the design you wish to build. The agreement is exclusively for the design portion, so you can agree on the design and conclusive project pricing before entering into a contract for the total contract sum.

What should I expect from the project?

We will build a full contact and production timeline with you after discussing your ideas. We want to know what your project aims are, the issues you're facing about it, and the allocated budget. We shall keep you informed at every phase once we start working.

How does the Home Improvement Consumer Protection Act handle emergency work?

Any job conducted under the emergency work requirements of Section 201-7 in the legislation of Pennsylvania's Unfair Trade Practices and Consumer Protection Law is not categorized as a home improvement under the Consumer Protection Act for Home Improvement. This page contains a link to that statute.

Gallatin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 4,946, making it the third-least populous county in Illinois. Its county seat is Shawneetown. It is located in the southern portion of Illinois known locally as Little Egypt. Located at the mouth of the Wabash River, Gallatin County, along with neighboring Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky form the tri-point of the Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky Tri-State Area.

Gallatin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 4,946, making it the third-least populous county in Illinois. Its county seat is Shawneetown. It is located in the southern portion of Illinois known locally as Little Egypt. Located at the mouth of the Wabash River, Gallatin County, along with neighboring Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky form the tri-point of the Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky Tri-State Area.

Gallatin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 4,946, making it the third-least populous county in Illinois. Its county seat is Shawneetown. It is located in the southern portion of Illinois known locally as Little Egypt. Located at the mouth of the Wabash River, Gallatin County, along with neighboring Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky form the tri-point of the Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky Tri-State Area.

Gallatin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 4,946, making it the third-least populous county in Illinois. Its county seat is Shawneetown. It is located in the southern portion of Illinois known locally as Little Egypt. Located at the mouth of the Wabash River, Gallatin County, along with neighboring Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky form the tri-point of the Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky Tri-State Area.

Gallatin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Illinois. According to the 2020 census, it has a population of 4,946, making it the third-least populous county in Illinois. Its county seat is Shawneetown. It is located in the southern portion of Illinois known locally as Little Egypt. Located at the mouth of the Wabash River, Gallatin County, along with neighboring Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky form the tri-point of the Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky Tri-State Area.
